## Output Format:
Return a JSON array inside <memories> tags. Each memory object should have:
- "fact": The self-contained atomic fact (string)
- "entities": List of people, projects, products mentioned (array of strings)
- "event_dates": List of ISO dates when the event occurred/will occur (array of strings, can be empty)
- "is_future": Whether this is about a future event (boolean)
- "temporal_refs": Raw temporal phrases found like "next week", "Q2" (array of strings)
- "confidence": How confident you are this is a real fact vs speculation (0.0-1.0)

<memories>
[
  {
    "fact": "John recommended the mobile-first approach for the Q3 product launch",
    "entities": ["John", "Q3 product launch"],
    "event_dates": ["2024-07-01"],
    "is_future": true,
    "temporal_refs": ["Q3"],
    "confidence": 0.95
  },
  {
    "fact": "The team decided to increase the marketing budget from $50k to $75k",
    "entities": ["marketing budget"],
    "event_dates": [],
    "is_future": false,
    "temporal_refs": [],
    "confidence": 1.0
  }
]
</memories>

